definition (en): Form of item other than microfilm, microfiche, microopaque, large print, braille, online, direct electronic, regular print reproduction, electronic.
scope note (en): Not specified by one of the other codes.

definition (en): Accessed by means of hardware and software connections to a communications network.
Storage on a directly accessible tangible recording medium, e.g. disc, tape, playaway device, flashdrive, portable hard drive, etc.
Eye-readable print, such as a photocopy.

Intended for manipulation by a computer. May reside in a carrier accessed either directly or remotely, in some cases requiring the use of peripheral devices attached to the computer (e.g., a CD-ROM player).
scope note (en): Not used for items that do not require the use of a computer (e.g., music compact discs, videodiscs).
